The paper deals with the performance evaluation of a broadband access network using DWDM and 1D-OOC techniques, which involves the use of optical sources with large spectrum bandwidth. This involves the study of error probability and interference in the network, which falls under the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), optical networking (cs.OH), communication (cs.COMM), and photonics (cs.PHOTONICS).
